                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm sure I'll be called 5 sorts of traitor for saying it, but I truly am not bugged by the charm changes.  As a play style, I didn't like when charm groups, especially with pet tanking, were considered "necessary".  I hated random pickup groups informing me that they'd take me for Vxed and btw they wanted me to finish the Vxed trial for them yet again (since they weren't qualified to finish it themself), without snare, and with half the group having no idea how to handle a pet.  Also, I don't feel that the power of CoD in some very specific instances is really fair to other classes, or even to other enchanters who don't have the time and resources to box themselves a mage, a druid, and a cleric.
<br />

<br />
I was wondering if anyone out there fondly remembers the days when group enchanter'ing was about mezz, and charming was something you mostly did as a solo or duo activity?</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
