                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If you don't like charm, don't use it. It's very simple.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I hate the Cripple line. I think it's a joke. I've never seen a parse of a mobs' DPS or flurry/rampage rate after Cripple to convince me otherwise. I would not miss it in the slightest if they took the entire line out and replaced it with True South.
<br />

<br />
But, dammit, you can bet if they removed it they'd better tell me why, and it had better be good. You don't go nerfing and modifying abilities just because you feel like it.
<br />

<br />
It's EIGHT expansions into the game now. You don't go completely redefining a class ability in one fell swoop unless it REALLY needs to happen. When it does REALLY need to happen, you don't do it with 3 days of beta testing and a single short paragraph from your PR guy telling the players that charm was changed so that 'the game would be more fun'.
<br />

<br />
They should've pulled out their big guns (not that I know who they are, I wasn't terribly impressed by Rytan, but at least he's actually working with the game schematics as opposed to just interacting with the community, so I guess him), the guys who actually make balancing decisions, and written a short ESSAY on why this change was necessary. THEN, they should've collected feedback from messageboards AND from their long and arduous testing process before they slap a major change like this into the game.
<br />

<br />
EDIT: Btw, I do agree that eventually we probably need to take a laid back, 'alright, it's time to let this one slide' approach, and hey, if you don't like using charm, more power to you - you probably cast Cripple more than me <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />. However, the wounds are still fresh here, and I think the way in which this change (justified or not) was implemented and explained was, quite simply, shameful.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
