                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Riart wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Make an appealing place for the people that come under SOE IP's to post and maybe they will actually post.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Even if I really really tried, I'm not sure that I could come up with anything that would appeal to SOE atm.
<br />

<br />
BTW.../wave Cat  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Cat is not a closet SOE person, her friend is not a GM and I am not an arsonist.
<br />

<br />
To the matter at hand, the charm nerf is not going to greatly impact my gameplay.  However, it IS a tool that was essentially removed from my arsenal.  Taking away my options to play a class how I choose to play it is terrible.
<br />

<br />
While there are a lot of posts about the charm nerf (due to it being underhanded and dirty), with this expansion we had several indirect nerfs as well.   Our highest spells in POP were 2 group buffs and a crappy illusion.  Not exactly class defining, at least, it wasn't at the time. <img src="images/smiles/icon_eek.gif" alt="icon_eek.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
So, now we have OOW charm nerf (OOW charm spells don't seem to work in other expansions)
<br />
Flagging of select mobs in BoT, Tactics, Vxed as UNCHARMABLE  (either straight out uncharmable(BoT) or uncharmable due to level and not mob model.
<br />
No upgrade to WoM
<br />
No upgrade to tashan line
<br />
No upgrade to debuffs (slow/cripple)
<br />
A REDUCED upgrade to self shield when comparing to other int caster upgrades.
<br />
No Magic resistance upgrade
<br />
Stun and nuke upgrades on a shared timer system making them negligable upgrades, at best.
<br />
NO aggro reducer upgrade
<br />
No new illusions/faction modifiers
<br />
No advanced dire charm aa
<br />

<br />

<br />
My personal opinion is charm is a biggie, but personally NOT the game breaker.  The game breaker to me is the long, long list above.
<br />

<br />
Everyone gets better when they level up.  Except us.  Where we were not downgraded (as in charm) we were not upgraded, which is, in effect, reducing our abilities, so as we gain in levels, we downgrade in power.
<br />

<br />
The cherry topper on this for me is EVERY OTHER class in game supporting all of this.  It makes me sad.  But when I zone into OOW, I always get one random tell....."KEI PLX"   <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
